<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" CalDefCategory="HMI" Description="GIS-621 - CSM Component Diagnostic Specification for Global A">
  <CalDefFileVersion>15</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>14APR14</Date>
    <Description>Reviewed for compliance to CalDef Guidelines. - Jon G</Description>
    <Author>David Bonello</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>2/17/2015</Date>
    <Description>Updated GIS-621 to version 1.7 GIS-621</Description>
    <Author>David Bonello</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>6/19/2015</Date>
    <Description>Deleted the DEBOUNCE_TIME CAL that was incorrected defined as a Boolean type CAL in the previous version of this caldef file, and replacing with a new DEBOUNCE_TIME CALCAL correctly defined as an Integer. Also, changed the default values for the B127B_2B, U0020_00 CALs from False to True  and default value for RECOVERY_UNDER_OVER_VOLTAGE CAL from 0 to 9 within this caldef file.</Description>
    <Author>David Bonello</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>8/13/2015</Date>
    <Description>Deleted the MANUFACTURER_ENABLE_COUNTER CAL, as the MANUFACTURER_ENABLE_COUNTER should not be a CAL. Also deleted the DTC_MASK_B124C_00 CAL, as this was added as a CAL in error.</Description>
    <Author>David Bonello</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>8/31/2015</Date>
    <Description>Added DTC Mask for DTC B0010 &#x2013; REVERSE GEAR SIGNAL CIRCUIT.</Description>
    <Author>David Bonello</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>11/6/2015</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS621_DiagnosticCalDefGlobalA.caldef file made a documentation only update to fill in the missing information description field for the DTC_MASK_U0020_00 CAL with the DTC failure criteria that has always been captured in the GIS-621 Spec. </Description>
    <Author>David Bonello</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>2/26/2016</Date>
    <Description>Within this caldef file , deleted the following: DTC_MASK_B126A_00 (APPLICATION DOWNLOAD PERFORMANCE), DTC_MASK_U240B_00 (Radio Dedicated Bus Off -No Additional Information. (Private CAN Bus between CSM and Touch Pad Module) ), DTC_MASK_U1101_00 (LOST_COMMUNICATION_WITH_INFOTAINMENT_CONTROL_TOUCHPAD), DTC_MASK_U0140_00 (LOST_COMMUNICATION_WITH_BODY_CONTROL_MODULE - CSM detects Loss of transmitted headers for 3 seconds), DTC_MASK_U18AE_00 (LOST_COMMUNICATION_WITH_INFOTAINMENT_CONTROL_TOUCHPAD_ON_DEDICATED_BUS_1 - CSMMaster detects parity errors of the transmitted headers for 3 seconds)  Also, added DTC_MASK_B124C_00 ( UNIVERSAL SERIAL BUS CIRCUIT 2).  Also made the following updates to how the DEBOUNCE_TIME CAL is defined: Changed the units from seconds to milliseconds, and updated the maximum and default values defined for the DEBOUNCE_TIME CAL.  </Description>
    <Author>David Bonello</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>5/13/2016</Date>
    <Description>Added the following new calibrations: DTC_MASK_B127E_00, DTC_MASK_B127E_02, and DTC_MASK_B127E_04. Changed the default values for the following calibrations: DTC_MASK_U18B0_08, DTC_MASK_U18B0_02, DTC_MASK_U18B0_04, and DTC_MASK_U18B0_0D. Updated the calibration description shown only for the following calibrations: DTC_MASK_B124F_41, DTC_MASK_B124F_42, DTC_MASK_B124F_4A, DTC_MASK_B124C_00, and DTC_IGN_CYCLE_CTR_MAX.</Description>
    <Author>David Bonello</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>5/14/2016</Date>
    <Description>Added the following three new calibrations for MY19: 1.) DTC_MASK_B395A_08, 2.) DTC_MASK_B395A_72, and 3.) DTC_MASK_U240B_00. Also, updated the default value of the DTC_MASK_U18B0_00 from True to False. And, changed the default values for the following calibrations: DTC_MASK_U18B0_08, DTC_MASK_U18B0_02, DTC_MASK_U18B0_04, and DTC_MASK_U18B0_0D. </Description>
    <Author>David Bonello</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>7/1/2016</Date>
    <Description>Changed the name of the GIS621_DiagnosticCalDefGlobalA.caldef file to GIS621_DiagnosticCalDef_GlobalA.caldef for this caldef file to be consistent with the specific naming convention being used starting in the initial MY19 CAL Database release to identify the caldef files that contain Global A specific calibrations.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>1/7/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS621_DiagnosticCalDef_GlobalA.caldef file for RTC CR#: 1248710, deleted the following eight calibrations confirmed no longer to be needed and to correspond to what is reflected in the latest released GIS-621: 1.) DTC_MASK_U18AF_08, 2.) DTC_MASK_U18AF_0D, 3.) DTC_MASK_U18B0_08, 4.) DTC_MASK_U18B0_0D, 5.) DTC_MASK_U18B1_08, 6.) DTC_MASK_U18B1_0D, 7.) DTC_MASK_U18B2_08, and 8.) DTC_MASK_U18B2_0D.</Description>
    <Author>David Bonello</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>1/26/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS621_DiagnosticCalDef_GlobalA.caldef file for RTC CR#: 1248710, added the DTC_MASK_B395A_3A calibration as a new DTC mask calibration reflected in the latest GIS-621. Also, updated the calibration description for the DTC_MASK_B395A_72 and DTC_MASK_B395A_08 calibrations to reflect the description shown in the latest GIS-621.</Description>
    <Author>David Bonello</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>13</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>14</Version>
    <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS621_DiagnosticCalDef_GlobalA.caldef, corrected the description reflected for the DTC_MASK_U18B1_02 and DTC_MASK_U18B1_04 calibrations.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>15</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefinition Description="U240B_00 - Radio Dedicated Bus Off -No Additional Information. (Private CAN Bus between CSM and Touch Pad Module)" Name="DTC_MASK_U240B_00" References="GIS-621 Section 22.4.5" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA">
