  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="U0073_00_HIGH_SPEED_CAN_BUS_OFF - The handler notifies the application by using a callback function. This callback function is launched by the handler whenever a bus off condition is reported by the CAN-controller. A routine () checks every 1000ms if a Bus Off condition occurred. If the number of Bus Off events exceeds a Calibratable threshold of a calibratable number of consecutive tests, i.e. an X of Y algorithm, then the Bus Off fault code is set. The X of Y algorithm shall be started and the counter for Bus Off events shall go from 0 to 1 when the application is notified by the handler that a Bus Off has occurred. Setting of Lost Comm DTCs shall be inhibited while the counter for Bus Off events is greater than 0. The CSM Module shall make provisions for these 2 calibration variables. For high speed buses the default value for Bus Off events shall be 5, and the number of consecutive tests shall be set to 5, i.e. x=5 and y=5." Name="DTC_MASK_U0073_00" References="GIS-621 Section 22.4.2" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA">
    <CalID>_F_6CYJVzEeO7UP4sq3M7sQ</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>5/13/16</Date>
      <Description>Initial release of Diagnostic Trouble Code</Description>
